caption: Live save, debounce, revert
tags: $:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage/editor
title: $:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage/editor/live-save
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The editor writes the profile body on every change — debounced at ~200 ms
so it doesn't fire on every keystroke.  No save button.

When you //first// open the editor on a profile, a snapshot of the current
profile is taken in `$:/temp/json-convert/editor/backup`.  A yellow
''Revert to backup'' bar appears below the validation banner once the
backup exists — clicking it restores the profile to its pre-edit state.
The backup resets on wiki reload (it lives in `$:/temp/...`).
